but did we win the war?

560
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:01,790
It was his idea.

561
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,480
He endangered our families.

562
00:40:04,730 --> 00:40:06,250
You are a murderer!

563
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:10,750
Yes,

564
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:13,500
it was my idea
not to open the city gate.

565
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:14,940
Once the gate is opened,

566
00:40:15,250 --> 00:40:16,600
more people will die.

567
00:40:22,190 --> 00:40:25,040
I thought my daughter
had been dead for ten years,

568
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:26,330
but I instantly recognized her

569
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:28,600
from the city wall.

570
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:30,000
My poor girl.

571
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:31,440
She died right before my eyes

572
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:33,690
even before

573
00:40:33,690 --> 00:40:36,000
she could call me father again.

574
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:37,460
My daughter

575
00:40:37,770 --> 00:40:41,460
died before I did.

576
00:40:52,660 --> 00:40:54,940
Father.

577
00:40:55,940 --> 00:40:57,940
Father.

578
00:40:58,710 --> 00:41:01,040
Mother, I want Father back.

579
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:02,690
You are to blame!

580
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,770
Give me back my child!

581
00:41:14,410 --> 00:41:15,290
What did you see?

582
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:16,910
Our home.

583
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:19,730
Do you know what I saw?

584
00:41:20,330 --> 00:41:21,020
Our home,

585
00:41:21,710 --> 00:41:22,580
Mr. Ji's home,

586
00:41:23,370 --> 00:41:24,160
Mrs. Ping's home,

587
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:27,000
and the homes
of all Yueluo people.

588
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:29,520
I'm not a hero.

589
00:41:31,272 --> 00:41:32,710
I don't want to be a hero, either.

590
00:41:33,940 --> 00:41:35,620
I only want to keep the land

591
00:41:36,390 --> 00:41:37,210
and homes safe.

592
00:41:43,710 --> 00:41:45,750
- Why do we have to have war?
- Beat you to death.

593
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,910
It's useless
even if he's beaten to death.

594
00:41:52,330 --> 00:41:55,480
My child won't be able to return, anyway.

595
00:41:57,370 --> 00:41:59,370
I will die sooner or later.

596
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:02,250
I might as well go
join my sister earlier.

597
00:42:04,745 --> 00:42:05,390
That day,

598
00:42:06,008 --> 00:42:07,910
I used a sword to threaten
the young city lord,

599
00:42:09,270 --> 00:42:11,500
forcing him and the elders
not to open the gates.

600
00:42:11,890 --> 00:42:13,540
I failed to save our kin.

601
00:42:14,290 --> 00:42:15,350
I, Xiao Wuxia,

602
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,750
will kneel and apologize.

603
00:42:25,790 --> 00:42:27,810
I vow that from today on,

604
00:42:28,500 --> 00:42:30,440
I will fight for Yueluo
until the very last moment,

605
00:42:30,910 --> 00:42:32,330
keep Yueluo away from war,

606
00:42:32,790 --> 00:42:33,850
and restore peace.

607
00:43:22,770 --> 00:43:23,940
What are you doing here?

608
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:26,890
The Shameless Cat

609
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:29,000
is crouching in the snow,

610
00:43:29,656 --> 00:43:31,020
and I'm worried he will freeze.

611
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:43,680
I'm not cold.

612
00:43:53,660 --> 00:43:54,640
I'm cold.

613
00:43:58,120 --> 00:43:59,480
It's not good for you

614
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:01,100
if they see you.

615
00:44:02,190 --> 00:44:03,250
I'm not afraid.

616
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:05,620
I'm Mrs. Xiao, anyway.

617
00:44:06,500 --> 00:44:08,180
Are you planning to abandon me?

618
00:44:09,870 --> 00:44:11,020
That was an expedient plan.

619
00:44:11,416 --> 00:44:12,730
Why do you take that seriously?

620
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,500
Who tells you an expedient plan

621
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,640
can't turn into a long-term one?

622
00:44:31,540 --> 00:44:32,350
Shameless Cat,

623
00:44:33,620 --> 00:44:35,330
come what may,

624
00:44:36,080 --> 00:44:37,460
I will always stay with you.

625
00:44:41,690 --> 00:44:43,160
I'm willing...

626
00:44:55,624 --> 00:44:56,960
What were you saying just now?

627
00:44:59,410 --> 00:45:00,750
I will tell you

628
00:45:01,350 --> 00:45:02,310
when the war is over.

629
00:45:36,784 --> 00:45:41,134
♪The slanting sunray refuses to leave♪

630
00:45:41,394 --> 00:45:44,744
♪The moon is fading off♪

631
00:45:45,714 --> 00:45:49,974
♪Frost on the sword, string of the bow♪

632
00:45:50,274 --> 00:45:54,154
♪Bond people together♪

633
00:45:54,724 --> 00:45:58,944
♪The wind heading north and
the wild geese returning from the south♪

634
00:45:58,944 --> 00:46:02,954
♪Who can meet again?♪

635
00:46:03,514 --> 00:46:07,464
♪Looking at the mountains far away
and seeing everything red♪

636
00:46:07,464 --> 00:46:11,704
♪Immersed in the passing years♪

637
00:46:11,934 --> 00:46:16,354
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

638
00:46:16,354 --> 00:46:20,244
♪Yet now I am left wandering
in this life♪

639
00:46:20,814 --> 00:46:24,934
♪Faint memories of the past♪

640
00:46:25,154 --> 00:46:29,004
♪All tell of parting sorrows♪

641
00:46:29,684 --> 00:46:33,924
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

642
00:46:34,164 --> 00:46:38,094
♪Amidst the wind, I suddenly look back♪

643
00:46:38,544 --> 00:46:42,534
♪The face that feels so dear to me♪

644
00:46:42,914 --> 00:46:46,354
♪Where are you now?♪

645
00:46:51,884 --> 00:46:56,274
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

646
00:46:56,274 --> 00:47:00,114
♪Looking back, it seems like a dream♪

647
00:47:00,634 --> 00:47:04,884
♪Don't forget each other
even if we're far apart♪

648
00:47:05,264 --> 00:47:08,944
♪Don't waste time♪

649
00:47:09,634 --> 00:47:13,824
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

650
00:47:14,094 --> 00:47:17,964
♪Taste all the vicissitudes of life
in a flash♪

651
00:47:18,574 --> 00:47:22,714
♪Though nothing is permanent♪

652
00:47:23,294 --> 00:47:26,744
♪I wish you well♪
